["1. The first step is to address the issues found from the static analysis. These issues are related to the import statements of the `javax.persistence` package. Quarkus uses the `jakarta.persistence` package instead of `javax.persistence`. Therefore, we need to replace all the `javax.persistence` import statements with `jakarta.persistence`.\n\n2. The `javax.persistence` package is used for Java EE's JPA (Java Persistence API) implementation. Quarkus uses the Hibernate ORM (Object-Relational Mapping) framework for JPA implementation. Hibernate ORM is a part of the Hibernate project, which is a Jakarta EE project. Therefore, the package name has been changed from `javax.persistence` to `jakarta.persistence`.\n\n3. We also need to update the `pom.xml` file to remove any dependencies related to `javax.persistence` and add dependencies related to `jakarta.persistence`.\n\n4. The `pom.xml` file should include the following dependencies for Quarkus:\n\n```xml\n<dependency>\n  <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n  <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-orm</artifactId>\n</dependency>\n<dependency>\n  <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n  <artifactId>quarkus-jdbc-postgresql</artifactId>\n</dependency>\n```\n\n5. The `quarkus-hibernate-orm` dependency includes the `jakarta.persistence` API, and the `quarkus-jdbc-postgresql` dependency is used for database connectivity.\n\n6. After updating the `pom.xml` file, we need to update the import statements in the `Order.java` file."]